To build a trajectory-monitoring router that solves the "Routing Plateau" by bridging DSPy (compile-time prompt/flow optimization) and RouteLLM (runtime cost/quality routing), we need a razor-sharp engineering boundary.
This is the exact functional scope for a production-ready repository. It bridges the gap between DSPy’s assertion layers and RouteLLM’s underlying API translation infrastructure.
